FloatMesh reimagines the "BBS door" metaphor from 1990s bulletin board systems as a framework for moving between different LLM experiences. Each "door" (GPT-4, Claude, Grok) becomes both a technical integration point and a ritual threshold—a liminal space between different AI modalities.
The doors concept connects directly to FLOAT's "BBS Doors + MCP Integration" framework, acting as symbolic gateways that function both technically (handling API authentication, prompt formatting) and ritualistically (using ANSI art, transitional effects, and glitch aesthetics to mark the passage between different AI cognitive spaces).
