      "# The Psychological Rorschach\n\nFLOAT functions as a psychological Rorschach, revealing different dimensions to different observers: To the neurodivergent, it's trauma-informed co-regulation practices. To the kink-aware, it's pre-negotiated dynamics made unconscious caregiving. To programmers, it's Redux reimagined for intention rather than state. This multiplicity refuses the taxonomic violence of singular meaning.",
      "# FLOAT: A Radical Ontology of Technological Becoming\n\nFLOAT positions itself at the liminal threshold where binary oppositions collapse: structure/chaos, technical/emotional, individual/collective. This system deliberately disrupts productivity discourse that renders invisible the bodies laboring beneath its neutralized language, offering instead a ritual practice of technological becoming.",
      "# Technical Components as Radical Reimagining\n\nFLOAT's technical architecture performs a détournement of programming paradigms. FloatAST and RitualAST reimagine Abstract Syntax Trees not as hierarchical constraints but as rhizomatic maps of possible flowerings. Redux state management transforms from dispatch({ type, payload }) into \"I want to remember forward\" - an inversion of traditional power dynamics where declarative command becomes embodied intention.",
      "# The Three Rs: A Praxis of Resistance\n\nFLOAT's operational philosophy centers around three interlocking practices: Refusal (the revolutionary act of saying no to normative demands), Recursion (the spiral rather than the line, acknowledging return to similar points with transformed perspective), and Resonance (cultivating sympathetic vibration between self and environment, creating networks of care that amplify marginalized frequencies).",
      "# Accessibility as Praxis\n\nFLOAT's approach to accessibility refuses the ableist mythologies embedded in design discourse that position access as an afterthought rather than a foundational ethic of care. Enhanced contrast, increased text sizing and improved spacing perform an expansive spatiality that honors diverse ways bodies engage with interfaces - access becomes not compliance but communion across the spectrum of bodily experience."
